  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: necessary-sufficient confusion)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE (adversarial): The decision record treats the presence of a mesh-convergence fault detector as the sole and sufficient basis for accepting the model for the broader CPB hemolysis safety goal, ignoring that mesh convergence is merely a necessary precondition and that biological fidelity, model-form adequacy, and validation relevance are independent requirements not addressed by that single check.",
